parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park or neutral, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The gear shift lever becomes stuck
the vehicle cannot shift out of park or neutral
the vehicle bucks or jerks when shifting
and the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the park pawl can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The gear shift lever becomes stuck
the vehicle cannot shift out of park
the park pawl breaks or fails
and the vehicle must be towed or rocked to release the parking gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power or control, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission warning light comes on
and the vehicle bucks or jerks when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and misfires can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Timing chain failure can cause the engine to fail, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Vacuum hose failure can cause the engine to run poorly, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
Engine oil leaks can cause the engine to fail, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Cooling system failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
Electronic module failure can cause the engine to fail, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to fall into the door, making it difficult or impossible to open or close, which can lead to safety hazards and inconvenience.
symptoms: The window falls into the door
the window regulator motor needs to be replaced
the window makes a crunching sound when attempting to close
the window regulator fails multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stress cracks on the windshield can impair the driver's visibility, leading to safety hazards and accidents.
symptoms: cracks are near the side columns at about 9.5 inches from the bottom of the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The convex mirror without the "objects in mirror are closer than they appear" warning can create a safety hazard, as it can distort the driver's perception of distance.
symptoms: The outside mirror is convex rather than flat
the mirror does not have the "objects in mirror are closer than they appear" warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front ball joint can cause the wheel to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.

The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the variable cam timing system can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to reduced power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential engine damage.
symptoms: and the vehicle has reduced power or drivability issues.
